<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-10-13T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-10-13T18:00:00-05:00" n="425" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d425">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">894.48B/198: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Woods</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-10-13T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 13,
                                        1923—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>219. Following for you.</p>
                        <p>“October 13, Number 23. Have purchased all commodities listed your
                                76<note n="33" xml:id="d425fn33">Not printed.</note> costing about
                            two and half million dollars. Advise Japanese Bureau we have additional
                            $3,000,000 now available for expenditure. Large quantities food,
                            clothing and shelter supplies available, here. If wanted cable specific
                            requisition. Payne Amcross.”</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>